      {
        "id": "E_mEMNn1zoLjYrxY",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Situation B. Using a Bar Diagram</strong></p><p>To find the percent of seventh graders who liked doing a fundraiser, Keeya put the percent on a bar diagram to make a percent bar. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "4J3Kksx4xfUgKdMW",
        "title": "Keeya's Bar Diagram",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "cq/images/keeya-s-bar-diagram.png",
          "filename": "cq/images/keeya-s-bar-diagram.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "jWTrQFmi2uGpNE09",
        "title": "Text 10",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>1. What do you notice about the bar?</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "7b0XVHZFoQDANYW2",
        "title": "Text 14",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Answers will vary.</p><p>Students may notice that one spot on the bar represents two quantities.</p><p>The bar counts with amounts in equal measure (counts of students on the top and counts of percents on the bottom).</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "J8n-x0ZcY1Sz0PtA",
        "title": "Text 13",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>2. How did Keeya know where to put 38 students out of 50?</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "DwMlS-BfBxfR3IOx",
        "title": "Text 21",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Since ther are 100 pieces in the bar, we would need to count by halves to get to the 50 students. So 38 would go on the 76th mark. Every two black marks represent 1 student.</p><p>OR</p><p>Every 50 students represent 100%.</p><p>                ↓÷ 50                                     ↓÷ 50</p><p>Every 1 student represents 2%. </p><p>               ↓× 38                                   ↓× 38</p><p>Every 38 students represents <strong>?</strong>%</p><p>                                                                 <u>76</u></p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "XxEVWtS-A-lh0VIr",
        "title": "Text 15",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>3. How can the bar help Keeya find the percent of seventh graders who like the fundraiser? </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "DLM6rHMf9-wMNOnl",
        "title": "Text 4",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Answers will vary. Students might say that if we can see where the 38 goes on the diagram counting one way (by halves), then we can count (by ones) to find what percent that is. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "z75Kvo2WNAYtVIzd",
        "title": "Text 12",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Situation C. Voting for a School Gym</strong></p><p>When school construction projects are proposed, voters often must agree on a tax increase to pay for the project. Voters in two neighborhoods were surveyed and asked, &quot;Would you vote <em>yes</em> for the construction of a new school gym?&quot; The table shows the results of the survey.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "fpkjHA0ST3f2Jfah",
        "title": "Neighborhood Vote",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "cq/images/neighborhood-vote.png",
          "filename": "cq/images/neighborhood-vote.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "FTJPhy0yiCVhqfYW",
        "title": "Text 11",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>1. Which neighborhood has more support for building a new school gym? Explain your reasoning.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "QIzfVGhDT10HvVFt",
        "title": "Text 18",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Green has 31 out of 100 in support of the gym while Flower has 17 out of 50, or a rate of 34 out of 100, in support. Some students may look at the number of votes. Green has more votes for the gym, but this is looking at the votes out of the context of all the votes.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Some students may not use percents, which is okay. Answers should incude percents and rtios/rates.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "gQIcVqFMEkzCPWac",
        "title": "Text 19",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>2. What percent of the people in each neighborhood voted for the gym? </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "pT34B6fdeaDbng6B",
        "title": "Text 17",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Flower has 34% support for the gym while</p><p>Green has 31% support for the gym.</p>"
          ]
        }
      }
